    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "OK I've had a look and I'm afraid I can't see an easy way for Edit with Emacs to deal with this use case. The text area isn't really a text area, it's a set of complex HTML markup that is updated by JavaScript (which it uses to update span tags and keep the input nicely contextually formatted). I'm afraid the only real fix would be for ipython to allow the use of plain div/textarea elements (perhaps as an option). Fortunately Edit with Emacs would track new elements added to the page so making it a simple toggle widget should mean it's picked up as soon as it becomes something Edit with Emacs can edit. \n"
  },
