    "created_at": "2014-06-22T14:51:21Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-22T14:56:09Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just to say I came up with my own solution for using \"Edit with Emacs\" in notebooks before I found this particular thread:\n- Install this [spellcheck extension](https://github.com/damianavila/mIPyex/tree/master/custom/spellchecker).\n- For any cell you wish to edit, simply use the text box created in the spellchecking area so you can then edit with Emacs.\n\nAlthough it takes two clicks instead of one, this approach works reasonably well and is preferable to editing text in the browser. EIN is also nice but it doesn't support many features I use in my notebooks (e.g. animations).\n\nOf course, I would be delighted if someone figured out how to chain these two steps together so we could add an 'Edit with Emacs' button directly to the notebook toolbar!\n"
